<paragraph blockId="7.[264,1324,283,1033]" pageId="7" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,588,283,309]" pageId="7" pageNumber="48">First sternal complex</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[609,683,284,310]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="6.[264,368,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[287,1304,446,1847]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[282,1305,439,1858]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 2. Empoasca margaritae n. sp." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173932/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="48">
Fig. 
<quantity box="[669,683,284,310]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="48" unit="m" value="2.0">2</quantity>
</figureCitation>
m) with sclerotized sternal bar bowed ventrad, well sclerotized dorsal apodeme with broad, barrel­shaped medial notch reaching sternal bar. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[264,600,363,389]" pageId="7" pageNumber="48">Second sternal apodemes</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[627,708,364,390]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="6.[264,368,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[287,1304,446,1847]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[282,1305,439,1858]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 2. Empoasca margaritae n. sp." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173932/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="48">
Fig. 
<number box="[693,708,364,390]" pageId="7" pageNumber="48" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
n) reaching abdominal segment 
<number box="[1129,1143,364,390]" pageId="7" pageNumber="48" value="4.0">4</number>
– 
<number box="[1158,1172,364,390]" pageId="7" pageNumber="48" value="4.0">4</number>
½ (length: 
<quantity box="[264,448,404,430]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="2.9" metricValueMin="2.1" pageId="7" pageNumber="48" unit="mm" value="0.25" valueMax="0.29" valueMin="0.21">0.21–0.29 mm</quantity>
, width: 
<quantity box="[564,749,404,430]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.25" metricValueMax="4.5" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="48" unit="mm" value="0.425" valueMax="0.45" valueMin="0.4">0.40–0.45 mm</quantity>
), tapered slightly to rounded apices. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="48">Tergal apodemes</emphasis>
not significantly developed.
</paragraph>
